---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Naman Chetwani"
  description="Personal website for Naman Chetwani."
>
  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-top">
      <nav class="top-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="nav-link current" href="/">Naman Chetwani</a>
        <a class="nav-link" href="/about">About</a>
      </nav>
      <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" data-theme-toggle aria-label="Switch theme">
        Light mode
      </button>
    </div>

    <article class="essay">
      <h1>hi, i'm Naman</h1>

      <p>I’m 15 and I am an engineer</p>

      <p>I want to figure out how to ask great questions.</p>

      <p>I&apos;ve dabbled across most realms of building things</p>

      <p>
        My long-term goal is to build tech that reduces humanity’s existential debt.
      </p>

      <p>
        current interests: ambient AI, mech interp, latent a2a protocols, economics,
        superforcasting, nihilism, existential lit/phil, fire technology, aerospace,
        inference-time structures
      </p>

      <section class="reading-section" aria-labelledby="favorite-writing">
        <h2 id="favorite-writing">Favorite writing</h2>
        <p class="section-note">I really like pretty book covers</p>

        <div class="reading-grid">
          <a
            class="reading-card"
            href="https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/579436/sapiens-a-brief-history-of-humankind-by-yuval-noah-harari/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <img
              src="/reading/sapiens.jpg"
              alt="Cover of Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="reading-title">Sapiens: A Brief History of Humankind</span>
            <span class="reading-meta">Yuval Noah Harari</span>
          </a>

          <a
            class="reading-card"
            href="https://www.hachettebookgroup.com/titles/douglas-r-hofstadter/godel-escher-bach/9780465026562/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <img
              src="/reading/geb.jpg"
              alt="Cover of Gödel, Escher, Bach: An Eternal Golden Braid"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="reading-title">Gödel, Escher, Bach: An Eternal Golden Braid</span>
            <span class="reading-meta">Douglas R. Hofstadter</span>
          </a>

          <a
            class="reading-card"
            href="https://press.stripe.com/the-art-of-doing-science-and-engineering"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <img
              src="/reading/hamming.jpg"
              alt="Cover of The Art of Doing Science and Engineering: Learning to Learn"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="reading-title">The Art of Doing Science and Engineering: Learning to Learn</span>
            <span class="reading-meta">Richard Hamming</span>
          </a>

          <a
            class="reading-card"
            href="https://www.lesswrong.com/rationality"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            <img
              src="/reading/sequences.png"
              alt="Cover image for A Map that Reflects the Territory"
              loading="lazy"
            />
            <span class="reading-title">The Sequences</span>
            <span class="reading-meta">LessWrong</span>
          </a>
        </div>

        <h3>Favorite morsels of wisdom</h3>
        <ul class="plain-list wisdom-list">
          <li>
            <a href="https://paulgraham.com/greatwork.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
              Great Work
            </a>
            <span class="wisdom-meta">Paul Graham</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://blog.samaltman.com/the-days-are-long-but-the-decades-are-short"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noreferrer"
            >
              The Days Are Long but the Decades Are Short
            </a>
            <span class="wisdom-meta">Sam Altman</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <h2>Some things I think are important:</h2>
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>thinking ruthlessly independently</li>
        <li>coming up with elegant ideas</li>
        <li>convincing people what you believe is right</li>
        <li>sidequesting on occasion</li>
        <li>doing things that I think about when I am not doing them</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        my theory is that if I get better at reflecting on how I implement advice and identify
        what I am bad at, at repeat fast enough, I can recursively improve
      </p>

      <p>
        I love people so reach out:
        <a href="mailto:naman.chetwani@gmail.com">naman.chetwani@gmail.com</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <a
      class="corner-link"
      href="https://github.com/coder-2011"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noreferrer"
    >
      github.com/coder-2011
    </a>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
